cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.NI, cs.CY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the security implications of using OP_RETURN to store arbitrary data on the Bitcoin blockchain. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper analyzes the impact of OP_RETURN usage on the performance of the Bitcoin network. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as the paper discusses the storage of data on the blockchain. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses the usage of the Bitcoin network to store and transmit data. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is less likely but still possible as the paper touches on the social and economic implications of using the Bitcoin blockchain for purposes beyond currency transfer.
